url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/TannerGilbert/Tensorflow-Object-Detection-API-Train-Model/master/images/train_labels.csv'
df_train = pd.read_csv(url, error_bad_lines=False)

In [22]:
# -redni ilo bounding boxw dla przedziau iloci wystpie bounding boxw klas, 
# wykorzystaj trzy przedziay: <=41; 41-44; >44. Podpowiedz: zgrupuj poszczeglne klasy w przedziaach,
# a nastpnie policz redni dla przedziaw. Dodatkowo zaznacz na wykresie ilo unikalnychklas w kadym
# z przedziaw. Zadbaj o prawidowe oznaczenie legendy wykresu.

# obliczenia dla zbioru treningowego
mean1 = bb_for_class_train[bb_for_class_train<=41].mean() # srednia ilosc bb dla pierwszego przedzialu
count1 = bb_for_class_train[bb_for_class_train<=41].count() # ilosc klas w pierwszym przedziale
mean2 = bb_for_class_train[(bb_for_class_train>41) & (bb_for_class_train<44)].mean() # analogicznie dla kolejnych klas 
count2 = bb_for_class_train[(bb_for_class_train>41) & (bb_for_class_train<44)].count()
mean3 = bb_for_class_train[bb_for_class_train>=44].mean()
count3 = bb_for_class_train[bb_for_class_train>=44].count()

d = {'<=41': [mean1, count1], '41-44': [mean2, count2], '>44':[mean3, count3] }
bb_p_splits_train = pd.DataFrame(data=d) # stworzenie DataFrame dla obliczonych danych

mean1 = bb_for_class_test[bb_for_class_test<=41].mean()
count1 = bb_for_class_test[bb_for_class_test<=41].count()
mean2 = bb_for_class_test[(bb_for_class_test>41) & (bb_for_class_test<44)].mean()
count2 = bb_for_class_test[(bb_for_class_test>41) & (bb_for_class_test<44)].count()
mean3 = bb_for_class_test[bb_for_class_test>=44].mean()
count3 = bb_for_class_test[bb_for_class_test>=44].count()

d = {'<=41': [mean1, count1], '41-44': [mean2, count2], '>44':[mean3, count3] }
bb_p_splits_test = pd.DataFrame(data=d)

df = pd.DataFrame({'Dane testowe': bb_p_splits_test.values[0],
                   'Dane treningowe': bb_p_splits_train.values[0]}, index=bb_p_splits_train.columns)

ax = df.plot.bar(rot=0,figsize=(10,11),title ='rednia ilo Bounding Boxw dla przedziau iloci wystpie bounding boxw klas')
ax.set_ylabel("Ilo Bounding Boxw")
ax.set_xlabel("Przedziay")
ax.annotate('Nad supkami zaznaczono ilo klas w danym przedziale', xy=(-0.48, 43.5))

i=0
for p in ax.patches:
    if i<3:
        if bb_p_splits_test.values[1,i] !=0:
            ax.annotate(bb_p_splits_test.values[1,i], (p.get_x() * 1.005, p.get_height() * 1.08))
    elif i>=3:
        if bb_p_splits_train.values[1,i-3] !=0:
            ax.annotate(bb_p_splits_train.values[1,i-3], (p.get_x() * 1.005, p.get_height() * 1.008))
    i = i+1

# Wykorzystujc dowoln bibliotek graficzn, narysuj na dwch dowolnych zdjciach
# testowych oraz dwch dowolnych zdjciach treningowych, wystpujce na nich bounding 
# boxy. Dodaj podpis do kadego bounding boxa z nazw klasy. Zadbaj o, to aby zdjcia
# wywietlay si poprawnie w notebooku oraz byy widoczne przy wyeksportowaniu do html. 
# Przykad (nie zwracaj uwagi na liczb na kocu nazwy klasy): 
# https://github.com/TannerGilbert/Tensorflow-Object-Detection-API-Train-Model/blob/master/doc/output.png

%matplotlib inline
from PIL import Image, ImageFile, ImageDraw, ImageFont
from matplotlib.pyplot import imshow
import requests
import numpy as np
from io import BytesIO
from IPython.display import display, HTML
import random
import time
import os

import math

for e in range(4): #dla 4 zdjec
    rand = int(time.time()*e/10) 
    
    if e<2: # 2 pierwsze zdjecia to treningowe
        # sciezka do folderu ze zdjeciami
        Image_path = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/TannerGilbert/Tensorflow-Object-Detection-API-Train-Model/master/images/train/'
        # wybranie losowego zdjecia
        img_name = str(df_train['filename'].sample(random_state=rand).values.item())
        # sprawdzenie ile bouding boxow jest na danym zdjeciu
        bound_nr = df_train[df_train.filename == img_name]['xmin'].count() 
        bounds = np.zeros((bound_nr,4))
        class_name = []
        # pobranie bounding boxow do zmiennej
        bounds[0:bound_nr,0] = df_train[df_train.filename == img_name]['xmax'].values
        bounds[0:bound_nr,1] = df_train[df_train.filename == img_name]['ymin'].values
        bounds[0:bound_nr,2] = df_train[df_train.filename == img_name]['xmin'].values
        bounds[0:bound_nr,3] = df_train[df_train.filename == img_name]['ymax'].values
        # pobranie nazw klas odpowiadajacym bounding boxom
        class_name = (df_train[df_train.filename == img_name]['class'].tolist())
    if e>=2: # ostatnie 2 zdjecia to testowe
        Image_path = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/TannerGilbert/Tensorflow-Object-Detection-API-Train-Model/master/images/test/'
        img_name = str(df_test['filename'].sample(random_state=rand).values.item())
        bound_nr = df_test[df_test.filename == img_name]['xmin'].count() 
        bounds = np.zeros((bound_nr,4))
        class_name = []
        bounds[0:bound_nr,0] = df_test[df_test.filename == img_name]['xmax'].values
        bounds[0:bound_nr,1] = df_test[df_test.filename == img_name]['ymin'].values
        bounds[0:bound_nr,2] = df_test[df_test.filename == img_name]['xmin'].values
        bounds[0:bound_nr,3] = df_test[df_test.filename == img_name]['ymax'].values
        class_name = (df_test[df_test.filename == img_name]['class'].tolist())
        
        # pobranie zdjecia
    URL = str(os.path.join(Image_path, img_name)) 
    response = requests.get(URL)
    img = Image.open(BytesIO(response.content))
    img.load()

        # rysowanie bounding boxow oraz wypisywanie ich klas
    for i in range(bounds.shape[0]):
        img1 = ImageDraw.Draw(img)   
        img1.rectangle(bounds[i,:].tolist(), outline ="red") 
        font = ImageFont.truetype("arial.ttf", 20)
        img1.text((bounds[i,2],bounds[i,1]), class_name[i],font=font, fill=(255,0,0,255))
    
    display(img)
